                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t18230409-53-viclabel284" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-53-victim547 t18230409-53-viclabel284"></join>, of Friday-street; I saw the box safe in the passage ten minutes before it was taken. I saw somebody going out of the passage - I went to the door, and saw Cooper running with the box; Kingsbury took him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230409-53-person552">
                  JOHN 
                  JACKSON
               <interp inst="t18230409-53-person552" type="surname" value="JACKSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230409-53-person552" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230409-53-person552" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable; Garratt came to me - I went into Friday-street, and saw Cooper go from the door with the box on his shoulder. I collared Till-yard.</p>
               <p>TILLYARD'S Defence. I am a stranger to Cooper, but was merely passing at the time the box was stolen.</p>
               <p>TILLYARD - <rs id="t18230409-53-verdict285" type="verdictDescription">
